The paper discusses the use of Deep Reinforcement Learning (RL) methods to optimize the allocation of supply resources in urban environments. This falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of RL in handling uncertain environments, which could fall under Robotics (cs.RO) and Systems and Control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the use of RL in handling constraints on resource allocation, which could fall under Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC).
